[[Image:tatertots.png|thumb|right|250px|A close-up photograph of a plate of Tater Tots.]]

{{ingredient}}

"Tater Tots" is a registered trademark for a commercial form of hash browns, a side-dish made from deep-fried, grated [[Cookbook:Potato|potatoes]], which are formed as small, squat, oval cakes and sold frozen.

They are usually eaten alone, dipped in sauces such as [[Cookbook:Ketchup|ketchup]], but are also used in [[:Category:Casserole recipes|casseroles]].

