{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Veritaserum| type=Device| features=Advanced potion| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']]|}}
== Overview ==
'''''Veritaserum''''' is a colorless, odorless potion that forces the drinker to tell the truth.
== Analysis ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
Since the wizards have access to an infallible truth serum, some readers have questioned why this cannot be used by the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Wizengamot|Wizengamot]] to determine whether a suspect is innocent or not; and it has also been suggested that it could have been used in [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Half-Blood_Prince|''Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince'']] in order to force [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Horace_Slughorn|Professor Slughorn]] to divulge what he knew about [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Tom Marvolo Riddle|the young Tom Riddle]]. However, anything so powerful would be bound to cause creation of counter-potions and counter-charms, just as a means for editing memories has sprung up in the wake of the creation of a device (the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Pensieve|Pensieve]]) for playing them back; and the author has stated, firstly, that Slughorn, being so powerful and cautious a wizard, is bound to have secreted about himself potions to counteract the effects of Veritaserum and other harmful (to him) potions; and second, that the existence of charms that prevent or alter the action of Veritaserum on suspects would make Veritaserum-induced evidence invalid in the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Wizengamot|Wizengamot]].
It is certainly true that, while Veritaserum is mentioned several times in the books, it is only successfully administered once, to an unprepared, [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Stupefy|Stunned]], and effectively unsuspecting victim, in [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet_of_Fire/Chapter_35|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']].
== Questions == {{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Questions}}
== Greater Picture ==
