{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Dreamless Sleep Potion| type=Device| features=Advanced potion| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire|Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire]]|}}
== Overview ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
'''''Dreamless Sleep Potion''''' is a complex potion first mentioned by [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Severus_Snape|Severus Snape]] and later by [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Horace_Slughorn|Horace Slughorn]]. Both Potions Masters used this potion as an example of how powerful potions could be.
[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Albus_Dumbledore|Professor Dumbledore]] recommended that Harry be given the potion after he confronted [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Lord_Voldemort|Voldemort]] at the end of the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Major Events/Triwizard Tournament|Triwizard Tournament]]. <!--hope this edit meets quality standards - this is my first wiki edit ~Wookie Kisser~ -->
