== Alphabetical Order ==

We should group characters alphabetically because otherwise, an "overlap" of characters occurs. Lucius Malfoy is a member of the Malfoy family, a member of the Ministry of Magic and also a Death Eater. This can make finding characters easier. --[[User:Roonil Wazlib|Roonil Wazlib]] 15:19, 16 August 2005 (UTC)
:If people need to find characters, then they should be using the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Index|Index]]. The list now can always be reorganized some but its purpose is to put characters into groups. The character should go into the group he/she/it is most importantly featured in. Families will always get the character under their listing. I'm adding a message at the top of the page. Your issue should really be solved by using the Index. The purpose of the Characters page ''is'' groups. Also, I understand that some clashing may occur (i.e. I think the Black family members shouldn't be listed under "Black Family" or at least not until we can write up info on some of the main members first), but we have to work with the groups as best as possible. -[[User:Withinfocus|Matt]] 00:42, 17 August 2005 (UTC)

I agree to a certain point. I think that the characters should be listed in some type of order such as alphabetical order within the specific sections. This is just needed for the teachers section which has no seen organization.  --[[User:Luckrider7]]

