== Character Page Locking ==

I've placed this section above the status section so that people will hopefully notice it. Since the Characters page is insanely long, and even though I placed a warning on the page to ask people to stop adding characters, I'm considering protecting the page from editing to avoid junk three-word additions by anonymous editors. Does anyone else support this action, and are there other pages that anyone would like protected? With all the recent activity here, it's becoming a task to manage pages within the namespace. -[[User:Withinfocus|<font color="#000000">'''within'''</font>]][[User talk:Withinfocus|<font color="#7A7A7A">'''focus'''</font>]] 15:36, 21 August 2006 (UTC)
:I am slightly concerned about this. As I go through the chapter summary, I do keep finding characters which are not mentioned here, but have a role in the books, and I have to take the time to add them. For instance,a  while back I found that we had no entry for Bartemius Crouch Senior, and I haven't yet needed to check if there is an entry for Ludo Bagman. If you're OK with me asking periodically to have a character added, then fine, lock it up. I'm doing a lot of adding to the Magic page as well; I'd prefer that one not be locked. [[User:Chazz|Chazz]] 08:06, 22 August 2006 (UTC)
::I won't lock anything for now then. We can let some time pass to get final characters in, but in the future I'd like to lock it once we think we have a sufficient set. -[[User:Withinfocus|<font color="#000000">'''within'''</font>]][[User talk:Withinfocus|<font color="#7A7A7A">'''focus'''</font>]] 15:23, 22 August 2006 (UTC)
:::Thank you. Case in point: I just had to add Armando Dippet. He's still a stub, but I'll template and fill him in over the next couple of days. He appears in CoS and HBP for sure that I can recall, and he may have a cameo in OotP as well -- one of the portraits in Dumbledore's office. [[User:Chazz|Chazz]] 08:22, 24 August 2006 (UTC)

== Current Status ==

I notice that we have a Rosier Evans, a Rosier, and an Evan Rosier on the Characters page. I suspect that Rosier (a Death Eater, probably mentioned in either the Pensieve scenes or in the return of Voldemort) is not the same as Evan Rosier (listed as a Slytherin), but I think Rosier Evans is incorrect. I think we may have to combine these into one or two over time. I am not suggesting we do anything immediately; but I would like to keep a note here so that when we see "Rosier"s in the chapters, we can then decide how to correct it. [[User:Chazz|Chazz]] 23:44, 5 September 2006 (UTC)

